subSubSection.paragraph:
Body oblong, moderately compressed posteriorly; depth moderate, body depth at pelvic-fin origin 73% (55–93%) of longest dorsal-fin length. Caudal peduncle moderately short, depth subequal to length. Head moderately large. Several sensory pores on underside of each dentary; pore behind symphysial knob of lower jaw in ventral view; pore covered by lower-jaw lip on each side of symphysial knob in ventral view. Several small sensory pores on dorsal surface of each interorbital canal at mid-orbit level. Postorbital sensory canal short, slightly extending ventrally from sphenotic spine base. Isolated postorbital sensory canal (shown in 
Fig. 1
) usually absent (including 
lectotype
) (rarely present in other specimens).
